  "markup": "\u003Cp style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\u0022 class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPurpose:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E To outline general expectations regarding working hours, schedules, and related practices for all employees, valuing work-life balance while ensuring business needs are met, and to comply with wage and hour laws.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; margin-left: .5in;\u0022 class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProcedure:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Col start=\u00221\u0022 type=\u00221\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStandard Workweek:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E The standard workweek for full-time employees is typically 40 hours. The Company\u0027s regular business hours are generally [e.g., 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM, Monday through Friday], but these may vary by location, department, or individual role.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWork Schedules:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Your specific work schedule, including start and end times, and any required breaks, will be established by your manager. You are expected to adhere to your assigned schedule and be punctual. Any changes to your schedule must be approved in advance by your manager. For non-exempt (hourly) employees, all hours worked must be accurately recorded using the Company\u0027s timekeeping system (see Timekeeping Procedures Policy).\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMeal Periods:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E For non-exempt employees, a meal period of at least [e.g., 30 minutes] will typically be provided for shifts exceeding [e.g., 5 or 6 hours], in accordance with state and federal laws. Meal periods are generally unpaid unless you are required to perform duties during your meal period. You are expected to be relieved of all duties during your meal period.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERest Breaks:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Short rest breaks (e.g., 10-15 minutes) may be provided, generally for every [e.g., 4 hours] worked, if required by state law. These are generally paid. Rest breaks should be taken at times coordinated with your supervisor to minimize disruption to operations.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOvertime:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E For non-exempt employees, all hours worked over 40 in a workweek must be compensated at the overtime rate (see Overtime Policy). Overtime work must generally be authorized in advance by your manager. Exempt (salaried) employees are not eligible for overtime pay.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlexible Work Arrangements (e.g., Remote Work, Flextime)\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Some roles or departments may be eligible for flexible work arrangements, at the discretion of the Company and your manager. These are typically formalized through a separate agreement and are subject to the Remote Work/Telecommuting Policy. Such arrangements must not negatively impact productivity, team collaboration, or client service.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExpectations for Communication and Availability\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E During your scheduled working hours, you are expected to be available for work, responsive to communications (email, phone, instant messaging), and engaged in your duties. If you need to be away from your workstation during working hours for reasons other than approved breaks or meetings, you should inform your supervisor.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConsequences of Violation\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Failure to adhere to established working hours and schedules, including consistent lateness or unauthorized absences, will be addressed in accordance with our Attendance Policy and Progressive Discipline Policy.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E"
}]]></Value>
